catching-pen
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a woolshed pen in which sheep are kept prior to being dragged on to the board for shearing, or a pen in sheepyards for catching sheep for dipping, docking, inspection, etc.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
